<paragraph id="C116101CFF86CF2DDF90F9C3FE28A78B" blockId="2.[159,762,1506,1948]" pageId="2" pageNumber="152">Diagnosis — Gnathosoma slender in ventral view; P-4, in addition to the medial seta, with a heavy anteroventral seta.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C116101CFF86CF2DDF90F95FFEA0A7DD" blockId="2.[159,762,1506,1948]" box="[197,334,1738,1762]" pageId="2" pageNumber="152">Description</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C116101CFF86CF2DDF90F96DFC2AA29C" blockId="2.[159,762,1506,1948]" lastBlockId="2.[826,1429,311,1688]" pageId="2" pageNumber="152">
Female — Idiosoma dorsally L 802, W 520, with a large anteromedial and a large posteromedial plate and five pairs of smaller lateral plates. Eyes absent. Anteromedial plate L 263, W 336, anteriorly with a rounded extension. Posteromedial plate L 482, W 300. Large anterolateral plate L 243, W 102; large posterolateral plate L 251, W 70. All dorsal plates and platelets without glandularia, but the associated setae present. Idiosoma ventrally L 867, W 502. Suture lines of coxal plates indistinct. Genital field placed between first coxae, L 57, W 94. Gnathosoma slender in ventral view. Palp (
<figureCitation id="59920C99FF86CF2DDA64FD9CFA69A31E" box="[1329,1415,521,545]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="3.[159,171,1888,1907]" captionTargetBox="[204,1353,319,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-4@3.[204,1384,307,1857]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1: Bharatavolzia arabica n. sp., female: (A) – idiosoma, dorsal view; (B) – idiosoma, ventral view; (C) – palp; (D) – I-Leg-4-6; (E) – IV-Leg-4-6. Scale bars = 200 µm (A-B), 50 µm (C-E)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5404086" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5404086/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="152">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
): total L 236; L: P-1, 8; P-2, 84; P-3, 52; P-4, 60; P-5, 32; P-4 anteroventrally with a heavy seta, medial side of P-4 also with a stout seta. L of I-Leg-4-6: 76, 96, 84 (120 to tip of segment). I-Leg-6 anterodorsally with a heavy seta, I-Leg-4 and I-Leg-5 anteroventrally with 1-3 setae. L of IV-Leg-4-6: 96, 106, 88 (140 to tip of segment). IV-Leg-6 anterodorsally with two heavy setae close to each other. IV-Leg-4 and -5 anteroventrally with a group of setae, one of these setae of IV-Leg-5 with large pectinations. All legs with large claws.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C116101CFF86CF2DDC35FC20FBAEA2F2" blockId="2.[826,1429,311,1688]" box="[864,1088,949,973]" pageId="2" pageNumber="152">Male — Unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C116101CFF86CF2DDC35FC4AFC9FA525" blockId="2.[826,1429,311,1688]" pageId="2" pageNumber="152">Etymology — Named after the Arabian Peninsula.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C116101CFF86CF2DDC35FBB9FC80A7A7" blockId="2.[826,1429,311,1688]" pageId="2" pageNumber="152">
Remarks — This is the fourth known species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="06A96B9FFF86CF2DDC8FFBDAFB80A558" authorityName="Cook" authorityYear="1967" box="[986,1134,1103,1127]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrovolziidae" genus="Bharatavolzia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F3DDCC0EFF86CF2DDC8FFBDAFB80A558" box="[986,1134,1103,1127]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="152">Bharatavolzia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, two species are known from 
<collectingCountry id="B9BE508CFF86CF2DDC2DFBE7FC58A5B5" box="[888,950,1138,1162]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="152">India</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="A5386DEDFF86CF2DDC96FBE7FBA9A5B5" author="Cook, D. R." box="[963,1095,1138,1162]" pageId="2" pageNumber="152" pagination="1 - 411" refId="ref17836" refString="Cook, D. R. 1967 - Water mites from India - Mem. Amer. Ent. Inst., 9: 1 - 411." type="journal article" year="1967">Cook, 1967</bibRefCitation>
), while one species is known from 
<collectingCountry id="B9BE508CFF86CF2DDC2AFB00FC41A593" box="[895,943,1173,1196]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="152">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="A5386DEDFF86CF2DDC91FB00FA67A592" author="Schwoerbel, J. &amp; Sepasgosarian H." box="[964,1417,1173,1197]" pageId="2" pageNumber="152" pagination="293 - 301" refId="ref18352" refString="Schwoerbel, J., Sepasgosarian H. 1980 - Wassermilben (Acari, Prostigmata, Hydrachnellae) aus dem Iran - Entom. Mitt. Zool. Mus. Hamburg, 6 (107): 293 - 301." type="journal article" year="1980">Schwoerbel and Sepasgosarian, 1980</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="A5386DEDFF86CF2DDC6FFB2DFC22A5EF" author="Cook, D. R." box="[826,972,1208,1232]" pageId="2" pageNumber="152" pagination="1 - 411" refId="ref17836" refString="Cook, D. R. 1967 - Water mites from India - Mem. Amer. Ent. Inst., 9: 1 - 411." type="journal article" year="1967">Cook (1967)</bibRefCitation>
erected the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="06A96B9FFF86CF2DDBBDFB2DFA7BA5EF" box="[1256,1429,1208,1232]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrovolziidae" genus="Bharatavolzia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Bharatavolziella">
<emphasis id="F3DDCC0EFF86CF2DDBBDFB2DFA7BA5EF" box="[1256,1429,1208,1232]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="152">Bharatavolziella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for species without eye capsules. The new species differs from the two other known species of this subgenus in the slender gnathosoma and the presence of two heavy setae on P-4 instead of one or none. Moreover, compared to the Indian 
<emphasis id="F3DDCC0EFF86CF2DDA78FAFDFA7AA440" box="[1325,1428,1383,1407]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="152">B. pallida</emphasis>
Cook the new species has a larger anterior extension of the anteromedial dorsal plate, and compared to 
<emphasis id="F3DDCC0EFF86CF2DDC0DFA44FC42A4D7" box="[856,940,1488,1512]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="152">B. cooki</emphasis>
Schwoerbel and Sepasgosarian from 
<collectingCountry id="B9BE508CFF86CF2DDA31FA44FA7AA4D7" box="[1380,1428,1489,1512]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="152">Iran</collectingCountry>
the large anterolateral plate is less slender. The large posterolateral platelet of the new species is much longer than the smaller platelet posterior to it, but in 
<emphasis id="F3DDCC0EFF86CF2DDC0CF9C8FC40A74A" box="[857,942,1629,1653]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="152">B. cooki</emphasis>
these platelets are much less different in size.
</paragraph>
